race.comment: WINEACLOCKSUMWHERE (3) led and scored comfortably here first-up without a trial, winning by 1.8L in a CL2. He'll be fitter for that effort and he looks ready to go to the next level this time in work. Maps to find the front once again and with that added fitness, he can bring up back-to-back wins. VONSNIP (4) settled out the back but finished with a wet sail in a 58+ here 13 days ago and the rise in trip is a big tick for her. She usually improves with racing and the better draw today can see her hold a closer spot in the run. Can make her presence felt. SQUILLIONARE (1) felt the pinch first-up over 1000m in a 70+ here. She usually improves second-up and the extra trip looks ideal for her. The inside draw gives Nicoll options and she's right in this if she's at her best. HEAD'EM (2) comes through that same race where he was only 2.1L off the winner after sitting on the speed. Sets him up nicely for this. THE MIGHTY BUTCH (10) can feature first-up.
